00:23:46,920 --> 00:23:48,440
even with metal detectors...

260
00:23:48,480 --> 00:23:50,760
even in this transit lounge.

261
00:23:52,320 --> 00:23:55,320
SIMON: Oh, it's so early.

262
00:23:55,360 --> 00:23:57,280
You guys wanna get coffee
or something?

263
00:23:58,720 --> 00:23:59,960
TRETIAK: Sure.

264
00:24:03,880 --> 00:24:05,760
Be quiet.

265
00:24:05,760 --> 00:24:08,040
SIMON: What is it
you request of my employer?

266
00:24:08,080 --> 00:24:10,440
TRETIAK: Do you know
what cold fusion is?

267
00:24:10,480 --> 00:24:11,880
SIMON: Of course.

268
00:24:11,920 --> 00:24:14,040
It's the theory...

269
00:24:14,080 --> 00:24:16,600
of nuclear fusion
at room temperature...

270
00:24:16,640 --> 00:24:17,720
free energy forever.

271
00:24:17,760 --> 00:24:19,000
TRETIAK: Yes.

272
00:24:19,040 --> 00:24:20,120
SERVER: Kaffee?

273
00:24:20,160 --> 00:24:21,240
SIMON: Klein, Bitte.

274
00:24:23,040 --> 00:24:26,720
SIMON: As far as science goes,
it ranks just above astrology.

275
00:24:26,720 --> 00:24:28,640
Those who claim to
have achieved the experiment...

276
00:24:28,680 --> 00:24:30,760
have never been able
to duplicate it.

277
00:24:30,800 --> 00:24:32,040
TRETIAK: Until now.

278
00:24:33,800 --> 00:24:37,720
There is an electrochemist
working at Oxford.

279
00:24:37,760 --> 00:24:40,040
We believe
that this good lady...

280
00:24:40,080 --> 00:24:42,880
made a breakthrough
in cold fusion.

281
00:24:42,920 --> 00:24:46,840
Your employer
will obtain the formula for me.

282
00:24:46,880 --> 00:24:50,520
He's very busy,
and you are very boring.

283
00:24:50,560 --> 00:24:52,320
Your offer must inspire him.

284
00:24:52,320 --> 00:24:54,840
This woman
has repeatedly avoided...

285
00:24:54,880 --> 00:24:58,560
my agents' attempts
to find the formula.

286
00:24:58,600 --> 00:25:00,600
She's cagey, difficult.

287
00:25:01,960 --> 00:25:04,160
Maybe your agents are stupid.

288
00:25:08,080 --> 00:25:12,000
I think this inspiration would
cost you three million dollars.

289
00:25:12,040 --> 00:25:14,240
TRETIAK: [Chuckles]
Ridiculous.

290
00:25:14,240 --> 00:25:18,840
SIMON: Why? You will have
the world market in energy.

291
00:25:18,880 --> 00:25:21,240
Cost you a nickel
for every million you make.

292
00:25:21,280 --> 00:25:22,520
His deposit should go--

293
00:25:22,560 --> 00:25:25,600
Hey. It is not for me.

294
00:25:25,640 --> 00:25:27,080
It is for mother Russia.

295
00:25:27,120 --> 00:25:30,880
But you want mother Russia,
too, Mr. Tretiak.

296
00:25:30,880 --> 00:25:34,520
Three million on deposit 
in a bank account in Zurich. Agreed?

297
00:25:36,680 --> 00:25:38,240
Yes.

298
00:25:38,280 --> 00:25:43,360
And... How long to get
your employer's agreement?

299
00:25:43,400 --> 00:25:44,560
I'll ask.

300
00:25:59,360 --> 00:26:00,920
Your offer has inspired her.

301
00:26:00,960 --> 00:26:02,040
I'll do it.

302
00:26:03,680 --> 00:26:05,840
Bank account number in Zurich.

303
00:26:06,720 --> 00:26:08,600
Auf wiedersehen. Bye, sonny.

304
00:26:08,640 --> 00:26:10,360
TRETIAK: Bye-bye.

305
00:26:11,800 --> 00:26:15,920
I really love this guy.
Ha ha ha!

306
00:26:18,960 --> 00:26:20,960
ILYA:
Too bad we have to kill him.

307
00:26:21,000 --> 00:26:22,360
Yeah, too bad.

308
00:26:36,880 --> 00:26:39,600
WOMAN: When the electrochemists
Pons and Fleischman...

309
00:26:39,640 --> 00:26:42,040
announced in 1989...

310
00:26:42,080 --> 00:26:45,160
that they had discovered
cold fusion...

311
00:26:45,200 --> 00:26:49,320
a revolutionary process
of generating energy...

312
00:26:49,360 --> 00:26:52,720
they were at first
acclaimed as geniuses...

313
00:26:52,760 --> 00:26:55,480
and then condemned
as charlatans.

314
00:26:56,640 --> 00:26:59,520
The protocols of cold fusion...

315
00:26:59,560 --> 00:27:00,920
SIMON: What are those? Drugs?

316
00:27:00,960 --> 00:27:03,960
Could I have one?
My head's pounding.

317
00:27:04,000 --> 00:27:06,040
She's boring the life
out of me.

318
00:27:07,800 --> 00:27:09,800
-They're for my heart.
-Oh.

319
00:27:10,920 --> 00:27:14,080
You have very pretty eyes.
You're a pretty lady.

320
00:27:14,120 --> 00:27:16,480
-Who are you?
-Me?

321
00:27:16,480 --> 00:27:18,920
I'm here to do an interview
with that Dr. Russell.

322
00:27:18,960 --> 00:27:21,560
I'm gonna expose her as a fraud.

323
00:27:21,600 --> 00:27:24,440
You don't put any stock in
this cold fusion mumbo jumbo?

324
00:27:24,480 --> 00:27:26,520
-Actually, I do.
-Really?

325
00:27:26,560 --> 00:27:29,640
WOMAN: Dr. Emma Russell.

326
00:27:35,760 --> 00:27:37,680
Oops.

327
00:27:42,040 --> 00:27:47,440
EMMA: Well, I didn't prepare
any formal remarks.

328
00:27:47,480 --> 00:27:49,360
I'm actually more interested...

329
00:27:49,400 --> 00:27:52,760
in what questions you all have
about cold fusion...

330
00:27:52,800 --> 00:27:54,840
so I thought we would
start with those.

331
00:27:54,880 --> 00:27:56,880
Any questions?

332
00:27:59,080 --> 00:28:00,160
Please?

333
00:28:00,200 --> 00:28:01,640
MAN: I have, Dr. Russell.

334
00:28:02,640 --> 00:28:05,720
Can you explain
the actual process of fusion...

335
00:28:05,760 --> 00:28:07,320
you know, the theory?

336
00:28:07,360 --> 00:28:10,080
Yes. Oh, there it is.

337
00:28:10,120 --> 00:28:13,960
This is the--the apparatus.

338
00:28:14,000 --> 00:28:15,320
And very simply...

339
00:28:15,360 --> 00:28:18,480
when positively charged
deuterons...

340
00:28:18,520 --> 00:28:21,360
are attracted
to the palladium cathode...

341
00:28:21,400 --> 00:28:22,800
they cram together...

342
00:28:22,840 --> 00:28:26,240
and there are millions of them
inside the cathode...

343
00:28:26,280 --> 00:28:29,520
getting closer and closer,
and then they fuse...

344
00:28:29,560 --> 00:28:31,640
and they create energy
in the form of helium.

345
00:28:31,680 --> 00:28:33,200
WOMAN: But I read somewhere...

346
00:28:33,240 --> 00:28:34,920
that the experiment
couldn't be replicated...

347
00:28:34,960 --> 00:28:38,600
so how do we know it works?

348
00:28:38,640 --> 00:28:40,720
EMMA: We don't.

349
00:28:40,760 --> 00:28:41,880
Not yet.

350
00:28:42,960 --> 00:28:44,760
But if you remember Einstein...

351
00:28:44,800 --> 00:28:47,800
he knew the theory
of relativity to be true...

352
00:28:47,840 --> 00:28:49,600
long before he could prove it.

353
00:28:49,600 --> 00:28:51,360
I mean, he felt the truth.

354
00:28:51,760 --> 00:28:54,800
And, uh, some of us
feel the same way...

355
00:28:54,840 --> 00:28:56,000
about cold fusion...

356
00:28:56,040 --> 00:28:58,400
because it's there.
It's in nature...

357
00:28:58,440 --> 00:29:03,000
the raw, natural power
just waiting to be harnessed.

358
00:29:03,040 --> 00:29:07,280
When we ignite
that cold fusion fire...

359
00:29:07,320 --> 00:29:09,520
I mean, just imagine.

360
00:29:10,600 --> 00:29:14,480
There's more energy
in one cubic mile of seawater...

361
00:29:14,520 --> 00:29:17,240
than in all the known
oil reserves on earth.

362
00:29:17,280 --> 00:29:21,200
I mean, you could drive
your car 55 million miles...

363
00:29:21,240 --> 00:29:23,600
on a gallon of heavy water.

364
00:29:23,640 --> 00:29:26,400
It would be the end
of pollution...

365
00:29:26,440 --> 00:29:28,880
warmth for the whole world.

366
00:29:30,360 --> 00:29:34,080
So why don't I demonstrate
for you...

367
00:29:34,120 --> 00:29:37,720
why other people in the past
have been so unsuccessful?

368
00:29:39,520 --> 00:29:40,960
They used very complex...

369
00:29:42,680 --> 00:29:44,960
SIMON: November 17, 11:30 a.m.

370
00:29:45,000 --> 00:29:47,520
Entering flat
of Dr. Emma Russell.

371
00:29:47,560 --> 00:29:48,760
High Street, Oxford.

372
00:29:49,760 --> 00:29:52,680
No alarms on outer doors.
Strange.

373
00:29:52,720 --> 00:29:54,280
TAPE: No messages.

374
00:29:59,480 --> 00:30:00,720
SIMON: Shelley Monument.

375
00:30:03,520 --> 00:30:04,800
Entering bathroom.

376
00:30:05,520 --> 00:30:06,960
Books.

377
00:30:09,320 --> 00:30:10,520
More books.

378
00:30:14,240 --> 00:30:16,840
Walls covered
with reminder notes.

379
00:30:18,880 --> 00:30:19,960
Poetry.

380
00:30:30,080 --> 00:30:31,200
[Click]

381
00:30:32,840 --> 00:30:35,000
Ah. 
Dad.

382
00:30:35,960 --> 00:30:37,720
[Click]

383
00:31:06,600 --> 00:31:08,760
"Stop and talk to Shelley
every day.

384
00:31:08,800 --> 00:31:11,280
"How can I love
a man named Percy?"

385
00:31:15,000 --> 00:31:16,920
"Isn't there
someone in the world...

386
00:31:16,960 --> 00:31:18,920
"who can consume me like that."

387
00:31:18,960 --> 00:31:22,080
Magic. Romantic.

388
00:31:29,920 --> 00:31:30,960
No recent applications.

389
00:31:31,040 --> 00:31:32,960
"Cold fusion notes."

390
00:31:43,920 --> 00:31:46,040
"Although I pass the
Shelley Monument every day...

391
00:31:46,040 --> 00:31:48,320
"its sadness strikes me
every time."

392
00:31:49,640 --> 00:31:52,680
"I feel a very personal loss
when I look at it.

393
00:31:52,720 --> 00:31:54,680
"So much pain
and so much passion."

394
00:31:59,920 --> 00:32:02,400
"To give light to them
that sit in darkness...

395
00:32:02,440 --> 00:32:03,880
"and in the shadow of death."

396
00:32:05,720 --> 00:32:08,280
"Luke 1; verse 79."

397
00:32:08,320 --> 00:32:11,200
Tretiak's wrong.
She's not cagey.

398
00:32:12,320 --> 00:32:15,160
She's not difficult.
She's just...

399
00:32:15,200 --> 00:32:16,440
eccentric.

400
00:32:17,120 --> 00:32:19,080
She's innocent.

401
00:32:25,400 --> 00:32:26,520
Maybe it's in her head.

402
00:32:28,000 --> 00:32:31,680
She needs a poet...
an artist...

403
00:32:33,200 --> 00:32:35,040
someone who...

404
00:32:35,080 --> 00:32:37,760
understands truth.

405
00:32:45,000 --> 00:32:46,760
She needs Thomas More.

406
00:33:15,480 --> 00:33:16,680
[Taps paper]

407
00:33:31,800 --> 00:33:33,080
SIMON: Do you like it?

408
00:33:35,240 --> 00:33:36,240
EMMA: What?

409
00:33:36,280 --> 00:33:39,360
The sculpture. Do you like it?

410
00:33:40,760 --> 00:33:44,160
Oh...yes.

411
00:33:44,200 --> 00:33:46,040
What do you love about it?

412
00:33:55,400 --> 00:34:00,480
The way it...glows.

413
00:34:01,160 --> 00:34:04,280
And how the light...

414
00:34:04,320 --> 00:34:06,840
holds him in silence...

415
00:34:07,880 --> 00:34:09,880
taking care of him.

416
00:34:11,520 --> 00:34:14,000
That's what I like about it.

417
00:34:17,560 --> 00:34:18,880
Are you an artist?

418
00:34:18,920 --> 00:34:24,240
No. I'm just a traveler
searching for purity.

419
00:34:25,159 --> 00:34:27,840
-What do you search for?
-Energy.

420
00:34:27,880 --> 00:34:29,720
Yes.

421
00:34:32,280 --> 00:34:35,120
Have you ever been
on a long journey?

422
00:34:35,159 --> 00:34:36,880
No, not really.

423
00:34:39,600 --> 00:34:42,159
Perhaps I'll take you
to my home...

424
00:34:42,199 --> 00:34:44,320
in Africa.

425
00:34:44,360 --> 00:34:46,840
You should
experience the energy...

426
00:34:46,880 --> 00:34:48,600
of where all life began.

427
00:34:54,199 --> 00:34:57,200
Sorry.
I'm not very good with people.

428
00:35:01,160 --> 00:35:02,880
Me, neither.

429
00:35:30,040 --> 00:35:32,960
EMMA: "I see my angel
for the first time...

430
00:35:33,000 --> 00:35:36,000
"know my purpose,
feel my birth..."

431
00:35:37,480 --> 00:35:40,680
"hear, at first faintly,
then distinctly...

432
00:35:40,720 --> 00:35:43,080
"the sweet strains
of our union..."

433
00:35:44,280 --> 00:35:47,680
"Our love heats up
the cold universe...

434
00:35:47,720 --> 00:35:50,440
"and gives my tired,
desperate hope..."

435
00:35:50,480 --> 00:35:53,240
SIMON: "purified
by our kisses...

436
00:35:53,280 --> 00:35:55,960
"are eternally healed."

437
00:35:57,560 --> 00:35:58,840
Do you like it?

438
00:35:58,840 --> 00:36:01,080
Who did you write it for?

439
00:36:01,120 --> 00:36:03,520
SIMON: You.

440
00:36:03,560 --> 00:36:06,960
You're following me,
or it's destiny.

441
00:36:07,000 --> 00:36:09,440
Either way, it's weird.

442
00:36:09,480 --> 00:36:10,960
Very weird.

443
00:36:13,440 --> 00:36:14,920
Destiny then.

444
00:36:25,360 --> 00:36:27,120
This must look strange.

445
00:36:28,800 --> 00:36:30,000
It's, uh...

446
00:36:30,040 --> 00:36:33,000
something that I'm working on...

447
00:36:33,040 --> 00:36:34,680
a formula for...

448
00:36:35,680 --> 00:36:37,800
creating energy.

449
00:36:38,400 --> 00:36:40,440
That you carry around
in your underwear?

450
00:36:42,080 --> 00:36:45,280
Yeah, I do.

451
00:36:57,680 --> 00:36:59,480
How did you do that?

452
00:37:01,400 --> 00:37:03,480
Magic.

453
00:37:03,520 --> 00:37:05,200
EMMA: Give it back.

454
00:37:05,240 --> 00:37:06,720
SIMON: It looks like Sanskrit.

455
00:37:06,760 --> 00:37:08,640
Give it back.

456
00:37:11,000 --> 00:37:13,840
I'm sorry. I just wanted
to watch you put it away.

457
00:37:16,000 --> 00:37:18,120
What else do you keep in there?

458
00:37:18,920 --> 00:37:20,000
Nothing.

459
00:37:20,040 --> 00:37:21,400
SIMON: That's not true.

460
00:37:23,040 --> 00:37:25,720
SERVER: Can I get you
anything else?

461
00:37:28,160 --> 00:37:32,200
SIMON: Drink your wine.
Latour '57.

462
00:37:33,800 --> 00:37:37,200
WAITER: The Latour, sir,
is $400 a bottle.

463
00:37:41,280 --> 00:37:43,400
Then we'll have two bottles.

464
00:37:46,560 --> 00:37:48,280
There. You count it.

465
00:37:54,240 --> 00:37:57,640
SIMON: All these little tubes
and microbes and things.

466
00:37:57,680 --> 00:37:59,000
EMMA: Molecules?

467
00:37:59,040 --> 00:38:01,080
-Those, too.
-[Laughs]

468
00:38:01,120 --> 00:38:03,680
EMMA: Can I tell you something?

469
00:38:03,720 --> 00:38:05,680
SIMON:
What? You must. Everything.

470
00:38:05,720 --> 00:38:08,160
EMMA: [Whispering]
It's a secret.

471
00:38:08,200 --> 00:38:09,320
SIMON: What?

472
00:38:11,200 --> 00:38:12,680
I'm done.

473
00:38:15,240 --> 00:38:18,360
My energy research--
I'm finished.

474
00:38:18,400 --> 00:38:21,680
I still have some sequencing
that I have to work out...

475
00:38:21,720 --> 00:38:24,800
to make sure that it's safe,
but I did it.

476
00:38:26,000 --> 00:38:29,440
It's just been you against
the whole world, hasn't it?

477
00:38:29,480 --> 00:38:32,040
How have you done it
and stayed so positive?

478
00:38:32,080 --> 00:38:33,720
The gift of faith.

479
00:38:35,480 --> 00:38:37,680
To see...

480
00:38:39,040 --> 00:38:40,360
Well...

481
00:38:40,400 --> 00:38:43,880
to believe in something
that's all around us...

482
00:38:44,880 --> 00:38:47,880
but hidden from our sight.

483
00:38:48,600 --> 00:38:50,360
SIMON:
That's a beautiful thought.

484
00:38:50,400 --> 00:38:52,400
EMMA: I can't believe
I'm telling you this.

485
00:38:54,000 --> 00:38:56,480
I don't even know your name.

486
00:38:56,520 --> 00:38:58,000
Well, my name is...

487
00:38:59,640 --> 00:39:01,080
I don't want to tell you.

488
00:39:01,120 --> 00:39:03,160
I don't want to do that.

489
00:39:05,000 --> 00:39:07,600
I don't want to do that.
What difference does it make?

490
00:39:09,880 --> 00:39:11,000
What's your name?

491
00:39:12,240 --> 00:39:14,440
-Emma.
-Emma.

492
00:39:14,480 --> 00:39:17,120
Now I know
everything about you.

493
00:39:18,400 --> 00:39:20,920
Your...genius.

494
00:39:22,880 --> 00:39:24,600
You have a weak heart.

495
00:39:28,160 --> 00:39:32,040
You have beautiful dreams,
great courage.

496
00:39:33,120 --> 00:39:35,600
You're not afraid in this world.

497
00:39:35,640 --> 00:39:37,520
You get that from your father.

498
00:39:39,760 --> 00:39:42,200
You can't cook
to save your life...

499
00:39:43,360 --> 00:39:44,640
and you love fish.

500
00:39:47,040 --> 00:39:48,600
I do love fish.

501
00:39:49,640 --> 00:39:51,800
That's weird.

502
00:39:51,840 --> 00:39:53,400
I want to try that.

503
00:39:53,440 --> 00:39:54,960
-No.
-Yes.

504
00:39:55,000 --> 00:39:56,920
I don't want you to.
Drink your wine.

505
00:39:59,320 --> 00:40:00,480
EMMA: Yes, I do.

506
00:40:01,760 --> 00:40:03,040
What's your name?

507
00:40:04,560 --> 00:40:06,960
My name is Thomas More.

508
00:40:07,000 --> 00:40:10,480
I was named after the saint...

509
00:40:11,960 --> 00:40:15,200
who died for his faith.

510
00:40:17,000 --> 00:40:18,120
OK.

511
00:40:20,560 --> 00:40:21,720
Your work...

512
00:40:23,160 --> 00:40:26,600
is very dangerous...
and alive...

513
00:40:27,840 --> 00:40:29,520
and I love your poems.

514
00:40:30,280 --> 00:40:31,640
They move me.

515
00:40:33,360 --> 00:40:35,160
But that's not
who you really are.

516
00:40:37,080 --> 00:40:38,480
You're running away from...

517
00:40:39,520 --> 00:40:42,120
your past and your pain...

518
00:40:42,720 --> 00:40:46,280
and yet you keep it
so close to you.

519
00:40:48,800 --> 00:40:52,480
So you don't have to be afraid
of who you are...

520
00:40:54,560 --> 00:40:56,400
because you're beautiful.

521
00:41:52,840 --> 00:41:54,120
What are you doing?

522
00:42:11,080 --> 00:42:15,920
EMMA: Oh, my God,
you're bleeding. What happened?

523
00:42:15,960 --> 00:42:18,120
SIMON: Don't know. I was...

524
00:42:18,160 --> 00:42:21,240
weeping, and I slipped.

525
00:42:21,280 --> 00:42:23,600
I was thinking of you.
I don't know.

526
00:42:23,640 --> 00:42:25,800
EMMA:
I live right down the street.

527
00:42:25,840 --> 00:42:27,520
I could clean you up.

528
00:42:28,800 --> 00:42:30,680
Why do you cover your mouth
when you laugh?

529
00:42:30,720 --> 00:42:31,960
-I don't know.
