530
00:42:36,320 --> 00:42:37,840
I'm glad it stopped bleeding.

531
00:42:39,840 --> 00:42:41,160
Don't need stitches.

532
00:42:42,920 --> 00:42:44,120
[Glass clatters]

533
00:42:47,840 --> 00:42:50,560
We're gonna have
to disinfect it, though.

534
00:42:50,600 --> 00:42:53,080
You really are an angel.

535
00:42:53,120 --> 00:42:54,280
You are.

536
00:42:57,440 --> 00:42:59,320
It's gonna hurt.

537
00:42:59,360 --> 00:43:00,640
-Aah!
-Aah!

538
00:43:00,680 --> 00:43:02,640
Oh, sorry.

539
00:43:04,760 --> 00:43:07,600
I'm sorry. Are you all right?

540
00:43:07,640 --> 00:43:09,480
Yeah.

541
00:43:09,520 --> 00:43:11,360
I'm sorry. I was just joking.

542
00:43:12,800 --> 00:43:14,360
I...

543
00:43:14,400 --> 00:43:16,440
-I should go.
-Oh, no.

544
00:43:16,480 --> 00:43:18,840
Yes. You--you...I...

545
00:43:19,840 --> 00:43:21,840
Take off your pants.

546
00:43:21,880 --> 00:43:23,000
Pardon?

547
00:43:23,040 --> 00:43:24,560
I mean, your sweater.

548
00:43:28,000 --> 00:43:30,880
EMMA: There's blood on it.
I'll wash it.

549
00:43:35,680 --> 00:43:37,000
SIMON: Very domestic.

550
00:43:38,320 --> 00:43:42,080
There's blood
on your blouse as well.

551
00:43:44,320 --> 00:43:45,880
I'll wash it.

552
00:43:59,720 --> 00:44:01,200
Do you have any wine?

553
00:44:12,480 --> 00:44:18,040
EMMA: I'm so overwhelmed
that you even noticed me.

554
00:44:18,080 --> 00:44:19,520
SIMON: How could I not?

555
00:44:22,080 --> 00:44:23,720
You make me feel so good.

556
00:44:23,760 --> 00:44:24,880
I wish you...

557
00:44:26,800 --> 00:44:28,400
I wish you could understand.

558
00:44:30,240 --> 00:44:32,960
I want you to know who I am.

559
00:44:49,320 --> 00:44:50,520
Oh, my heart.

560
00:44:51,560 --> 00:44:53,920
Don't disappear.
I'll be right back.

561
00:44:53,960 --> 00:44:56,680
FEMALE VOCALIST:
Calm it down.

562
00:44:57,400 --> 00:44:59,240
Bring it round.

563
00:44:59,280 --> 00:45:03,120
Too way high up, your street.

564
00:45:04,800 --> 00:45:07,720
I can see...

565
00:45:07,760 --> 00:45:10,240
like nothin' else...

566
00:45:10,280 --> 00:45:13,680
in me, you're better
than I wanna be.

567
00:45:15,920 --> 00:45:19,080
Don't think,
'cause I understand...

568
00:45:19,080 --> 00:45:20,440
Don't think,
'cause I understand...

569
00:45:20,480 --> 00:45:22,200
I care...

570
00:45:22,240 --> 00:45:24,640
Don't think,
'cause I'm talking...

571
00:45:24,680 --> 00:45:27,280
SIMON: Oh, I can't do this.

572
00:45:27,320 --> 00:45:28,520
She's so great.

573
00:45:28,560 --> 00:45:29,920
EMMA: I can't believe this.

574
00:45:29,960 --> 00:45:32,400
I can't believe
this is happening.

575
00:45:33,160 --> 00:45:36,040
VOCALIST: I'm open...

576
00:45:36,040 --> 00:45:38,920
to falling from grace.

577
00:45:50,920 --> 00:45:52,840
[Song continues faintly]

578
00:45:58,040 --> 00:45:59,240
EMMA: Hi.

579
00:46:15,520 --> 00:46:17,400
ILYA: "To spider:

580
00:46:17,480 --> 00:46:20,080
"Must fly. Have better offer."

581
00:46:20,840 --> 00:46:23,240
Greedy westerner.
Wants more money.

582
00:46:23,280 --> 00:46:24,480
TRETIAK: Who cares?

583
00:46:24,520 --> 00:46:27,400
Can't spend hard currency
in hell.

584
00:46:29,440 --> 00:46:31,120
Send this message--

585
00:46:31,160 --> 00:46:34,360
"Fly, don't buzz off.

586
00:46:35,720 --> 00:46:37,800
"I'll double your fee...

587
00:46:39,120 --> 00:46:43,360
"or send my own boys
to take care of the woman."

588
00:46:50,720 --> 00:46:52,640
EMMA: You OK?

589
00:46:54,440 --> 00:46:59,160
SIMON: Let's...
let's just lie here.

590
00:47:01,240 --> 00:47:03,840
Can't we just
be like this tonight?

591
00:47:05,680 --> 00:47:07,720
Is that what you want?

592
00:47:08,400 --> 00:47:10,160
SIMON: It's so magic.

593
00:47:15,960 --> 00:47:17,720
It just feels so perfect.

594
00:47:21,120 --> 00:47:22,120
[Beeping]

595
00:47:47,400 --> 00:47:49,960
RADIO: It's 7:00 a.m.,
and here are the news headlines.

596
00:47:58,680 --> 00:48:00,080
EMMA: Thomas?

597
00:49:13,640 --> 00:49:16,160
TRETIAK: Lev Naumovitch,
it's here! Good man!

598
00:49:16,200 --> 00:49:17,640
DR. BOTVIN:
It's revolutionary, sir!

599
00:49:17,640 --> 00:49:20,600
She's boldly cast aside
a slew of stale ideas...

600
00:49:20,640 --> 00:49:23,080
but I think the formula
is incomplete.

601
00:49:23,120 --> 00:49:24,200
It will take months...

602
00:49:24,240 --> 00:49:25,440
TRETIAK: That won't do...

603
00:49:25,480 --> 00:49:28,360
because now that the people are
nicely beginning to freeze...

604
00:49:28,400 --> 00:49:31,960
Tretiak must sweep in
with a miracle to save them.

605
00:49:32,000 --> 00:49:34,240
MAN: How high do you want it,
Mr. Tretiak?

606
00:49:34,280 --> 00:49:36,640
TRETIAK: To the top.
Good morning, Yuri.

607
00:49:36,680 --> 00:49:37,920
YURI: Good morning.

608
00:49:37,960 --> 00:49:40,880
BOTVIN: Perhaps I
can confirm the validity...

609
00:49:40,920 --> 00:49:43,520
of this formula more quickly
if I dispense...

610
00:49:43,560 --> 00:49:46,400
with certain protocols.
But, Mr. Tretiak--

611
00:49:46,440 --> 00:49:48,520
YURI: How long, Dr. Botvin,
since you received...

612
00:49:48,560 --> 00:49:52,240
your last salary check
from Moscow University?

613
00:49:52,280 --> 00:49:55,120
BOTVIN:
Ukrainian Independence Day.

614
00:49:56,720 --> 00:49:57,840
Last August.

615
00:49:57,880 --> 00:50:00,280
[Beeping]

616
00:50:00,320 --> 00:50:02,520
Ivan, he's on-line.

617
00:50:04,520 --> 00:50:05,600
TRETIAK: Do it.

618
00:50:08,840 --> 00:50:10,000
SIMON: To spider...

619
00:50:12,280 --> 00:50:13,840
You've got the recipe.

620
00:50:13,880 --> 00:50:15,080
YURI: "Where's my dough?"

621
00:50:15,120 --> 00:50:17,120
TRETIAK: To human fly...

622
00:50:18,360 --> 00:50:21,560
Recipe incomplete.

623
00:50:21,600 --> 00:50:23,520
The cake won't rise.

624
00:50:23,560 --> 00:50:26,440
Hence, no dough.

625
00:50:32,600 --> 00:50:34,840
SIMON: I am not the baker...

626
00:50:34,880 --> 00:50:37,400
YURI: "...but don't make me
the butcher."

627
00:50:39,600 --> 00:50:41,320
I like this guy.

628
00:50:45,320 --> 00:50:48,240
No play, no pay.

629
00:50:48,280 --> 00:50:51,760
I'm certain you kept
the cookbook.

630
00:51:00,040 --> 00:51:01,120
ILYA: Holland Park.

631
00:51:16,080 --> 00:51:17,760
RECEPTIONIST:
I'll check that for you.

632
00:51:17,800 --> 00:51:20,800
Yes, that seems to be fine.
One moment. Aah!

633
00:51:29,720 --> 00:51:31,360
SIMON: He's keeping me on-line.

634
00:51:40,800 --> 00:51:42,040
MAN: You wait here.

635
00:51:57,200 --> 00:51:59,840
[Sirens]

636
00:52:07,480 --> 00:52:09,320
[Beeping]

637
00:52:09,320 --> 00:52:10,440
[Beeping]

638
00:52:23,600 --> 00:52:26,240
POLICE OFFICER:
You, beside the car.

639
00:52:27,320 --> 00:52:31,000
Now, turn around.
Step away from the vehicle.

640
00:52:31,040 --> 00:52:32,160
SIMON: He's armed!

641
00:52:54,680 --> 00:52:55,800
ILYA: Drive!

642
00:53:05,040 --> 00:53:07,400
ILYA: Go the other way. Go!

643
00:53:12,120 --> 00:53:14,320
MALE VOCALIST:
You're all I've got tonight.

644
00:53:15,720 --> 00:53:18,200
You're all I've got tonight.

645
00:53:20,360 --> 00:53:21,640
INSPECTOR: What about him?

646
00:53:29,960 --> 00:53:31,480
What about this one?

647
00:53:36,000 --> 00:53:38,280
EMMA: Yeah. That--

648
00:53:38,320 --> 00:53:41,480
INSPECTOR: You see. We believe
they're all the same villain.

649
00:53:46,080 --> 00:53:47,480
Oh, my God.

650
00:53:49,440 --> 00:53:51,560
They're all him?

651
00:53:51,600 --> 00:53:53,240
INSPECTOR: We believe so.

652
00:53:53,280 --> 00:53:56,120
He eluded a hit squad
this morning in Holland Park.

653
00:53:58,320 --> 00:54:00,720
Then he fled the U.K.
out of Heathrow.

654
00:54:00,760 --> 00:54:02,480
WOMAN: We've got a handful
of false identities...

655
00:54:02,520 --> 00:54:05,880
used on visas,
passports, leases...

656
00:54:07,080 --> 00:54:08,320
Nicholas Owen...

657
00:54:08,320 --> 00:54:10,440
Louie Guanella...

658
00:54:10,480 --> 00:54:11,640
Peter Damian...

659
00:54:13,040 --> 00:54:15,200
Charles Borroneo.

660
00:54:15,240 --> 00:54:17,680
EMMA: Of course.

661
00:54:17,720 --> 00:54:20,400
Thomas More.

662
00:54:20,440 --> 00:54:22,440
All names of Catholic saints.

663
00:54:25,800 --> 00:54:28,200
Can you access
Heathrow's passenger lists...

664
00:54:28,240 --> 00:54:31,200
for the last eight hours?

665
00:54:31,800 --> 00:54:33,400
I think it might be possible.

666
00:54:33,440 --> 00:54:34,560
Good.

667
00:54:38,440 --> 00:54:39,880
[Bell rings]

668
00:54:39,920 --> 00:54:41,440
[Crowd cheering]

669
00:54:42,400 --> 00:54:43,520
ILYA: Go!

670
00:55:01,320 --> 00:55:02,400
CROWD: Yeah!

671
00:55:08,240 --> 00:55:09,800
[Singing in Russian]

672
00:55:13,680 --> 00:55:14,800
MAN: Yes!

673
00:55:26,120 --> 00:55:27,560
TRETIAK: See, my friends...

674
00:55:28,280 --> 00:55:31,240
you back the biggest rats.

675
00:55:33,600 --> 00:55:35,520
[Speaking Russian]

676
00:55:51,560 --> 00:55:52,680
Hello.

677
00:55:56,560 --> 00:55:58,040
TRETIAK: Out, out.

678
00:55:58,120 --> 00:56:00,480
Freeloaders, out.

679
00:56:00,480 --> 00:56:02,080
I want to drink alone.

680
00:56:02,120 --> 00:56:03,360
Close the curtain.

681
00:56:24,960 --> 00:56:26,680
-What?
-What?

682
00:56:29,080 --> 00:56:31,040
SIMON: Don't look down.

683
00:56:31,080 --> 00:56:32,920
You know who I am?

684
00:56:34,080 --> 00:56:35,200
No.

685
00:56:35,240 --> 00:56:38,840
I'm the thief
you tried to cheat.

686
00:56:38,880 --> 00:56:41,720
This is your accountant.

687
00:56:43,960 --> 00:56:45,400
Talk to him.

688
00:56:48,040 --> 00:56:50,480
SIMON: The phone goes
the other way, you moron.

689
00:56:54,000 --> 00:56:55,560
Hello.

690
00:56:55,600 --> 00:56:57,200
Tretiak speaking.

691
00:56:58,040 --> 00:57:02,440
That money to Zurich,
send it now.

692
00:57:02,480 --> 00:57:03,960
I said now.

693
00:57:05,400 --> 00:57:06,640
Yeah.

694
00:57:09,160 --> 00:57:10,280
Thank you.

695
00:57:11,280 --> 00:57:15,000
You know what the hardest part
about being you is?

696
00:57:15,040 --> 00:57:17,560
Pretending to be so bad in bed.

697
00:57:19,440 --> 00:57:21,640
You son of the bitch.

698
00:57:22,360 --> 00:57:24,720
SIMON: There is an impostor.
Get him out.

699
00:57:24,760 --> 00:57:27,240
TRETIAK: Hey, hey, hey!

700
00:57:27,280 --> 00:57:30,840
Take your hands off me,
you idiots!

701
00:57:30,880 --> 00:57:33,160
Are you crazy? It's me.

702
00:57:33,200 --> 00:57:34,320
Go, go!

703
00:57:34,360 --> 00:57:35,680
Catch him, go!

704
00:57:35,680 --> 00:57:37,560
Ilya, get the bastard!

705
00:57:44,680 --> 00:57:46,600
[Siren]

706
00:57:50,320 --> 00:57:51,920
[Radio dispatcher
speaking Russian]

707
00:57:59,480 --> 00:58:01,760
SIMON: Fifty million. I'm out.

708
00:58:04,240 --> 00:58:06,160
SIMON: Mr. Ferrer checking out.

709
00:58:06,200 --> 00:58:08,720
CLERK: OK.
[Speaking Russian]

710
00:58:13,280 --> 00:58:15,200
[Speaking Russian]

711
00:58:18,200 --> 00:58:20,600
EMMA: I'll have one, too.

712
00:58:21,200 --> 00:58:22,280
SIMON: Emma.

713
00:58:22,320 --> 00:58:24,160
EMMA: Hi.

714
00:58:25,120 --> 00:58:27,720
I'm...I'm overwhelmed.

715
00:58:29,480 --> 00:58:30,560
You found me.

716
00:58:30,600 --> 00:58:32,200
Wasn't very hard.

717
00:58:33,440 --> 00:58:37,040
Two men with saint's names
flew into Moscow yesterday.

718
00:58:37,080 --> 00:58:41,000
Isadore Bakanja
is a short, bald African...

719
00:58:41,040 --> 00:58:43,440
whereas Vincent Ferrer--

720
00:58:43,480 --> 00:58:45,520
SIMON: Named after a saint
who betrayed his best friend.

721
00:58:45,560 --> 00:58:47,440
How could you do it?

722
00:58:47,920 --> 00:58:49,800
Emma...

723
00:58:49,840 --> 00:58:52,440
I--I had to.

724
00:58:53,760 --> 00:58:54,960
I'm a thief.

725
00:58:55,000 --> 00:58:56,920
I want my cards back.

726
00:58:56,960 --> 00:58:58,880
SIMON: You flew all this way
for your cards?

727
00:58:58,920 --> 00:59:00,000
Yes, I did.

728
00:59:00,040 --> 00:59:02,600
No.
It's because you're in love.

729
00:59:06,240 --> 00:59:07,480
I rest my case.

730
00:59:07,520 --> 00:59:09,280
Who are you?

731
00:59:09,320 --> 00:59:12,360
No one has a clue,
least of all me.

732
00:59:12,400 --> 00:59:16,040
EMMA: And why would you
steal cold fusion?

733
00:59:16,080 --> 00:59:19,280
It's free.
Why would you do that?

734
00:59:19,320 --> 00:59:21,320
[Bartender speaking Russian]

735
00:59:21,360 --> 00:59:23,000
Eight million reasons.

736
00:59:23,040 --> 00:59:25,640
Eight million.
Wow. That's all?

737
00:59:27,320 --> 00:59:30,680
I would have
given them to you...

738
00:59:30,720 --> 00:59:32,520
if you'd only asked.

739
00:59:38,680 --> 00:59:40,000
You've got
to get away from me.

740
00:59:40,040 --> 00:59:43,360
I'm not going until you tell me
why you lied to me.

741
00:59:43,400 --> 00:59:45,880
-You lied to me.
-I lied to you?

742
00:59:45,920 --> 00:59:48,360
You almost got me killed.
The guy says it doesn't work.

743
00:59:48,400 --> 00:59:50,120
Well, screw him.

744
00:59:50,160 --> 00:59:52,360
I don't think you'd enjoy that.

745
00:59:52,400 --> 00:59:54,280
EMMA: You're right.
I don't think I would.

746
00:59:56,360 --> 00:59:57,760
[Speaking Russian]

747
01:00:01,640 --> 01:00:04,640
Emma, you don't know
what you're dealing with here.

748
01:00:06,240 --> 01:00:07,640
EMMA: What?

749
01:00:16,040 --> 01:00:17,680
-They took my pills.
-No, they didn't.

750
01:00:17,720 --> 01:00:19,720
I palmed them from your purse.

751
01:00:19,760 --> 01:00:21,880
I need one or two.

752
01:00:21,920 --> 01:00:24,960
I need...
I have a bad heart.

753
01:00:25,000 --> 01:00:27,680
-I know.
-It's starting to pound.

754
01:00:27,680 --> 01:00:29,160
SIMON:
It's OK. I've got your pills.

755
01:00:29,160 --> 01:00:30,280
OK, I've got two in my hand.

756
01:00:30,280 --> 01:00:33,000
OK, I've got two in my hand.

757
01:00:33,000 --> 01:00:34,200
EMMA: I'm gonna pass out.

758
01:00:34,240 --> 01:00:36,040
Sit down on the floor.

759
01:00:37,600 --> 01:00:40,680
Just get down on the floor.
That's right.

760
01:00:40,720 --> 01:00:42,480
That's right.
Eat two out of my hand.

761
01:00:42,520 --> 01:00:45,920
That's right. OK?

762
01:00:45,960 --> 01:00:48,320
While you're down there...

763
01:00:50,960 --> 01:00:52,840
Get the pocketknife
out of my boot.

764
01:00:55,400 --> 01:00:59,080
This formula makes
certain assumptions...

765
01:00:59,120 --> 01:01:03,320
which contradict all we know
about cold fusion cathodes...

766
01:01:03,360 --> 01:01:05,520
so testing at any level
becomes futile...

767
01:01:05,560 --> 01:01:09,120
without further information,
Mr. Tretiak.

768
01:01:09,160 --> 01:01:11,840
TRETIAK:
Don't despair, Dr. Botvin.

769
01:01:11,880 --> 01:01:13,280
Help is here.

770
01:01:24,440 --> 01:01:26,160
The two came very quietly.

771
01:01:28,440 --> 01:01:29,600
Oh.

772
01:01:34,640 --> 01:01:37,320
TRETIAK:
And they left even more quietly.

773
01:01:39,000 --> 01:01:40,360
Close the city.

774
01:01:40,800 --> 01:01:45,400
Kill him, and bring her...alive.

775
01:01:45,440 --> 01:01:46,840
[Sirens]

776
01:01:59,040 --> 01:02:01,800
Why are they after me?

777
01:02:01,840 --> 01:02:05,960
Tretiak, the guy I work for...
he owns this city, cops and all.

778
01:02:06,000 --> 01:02:10,120
We have to convince him there's
nothing more he wants from you.

779
01:02:10,120 --> 01:02:12,160
EMMA: What do you want from me?

780
01:02:18,040 --> 01:02:21,440
-Everything's on those cards?
-Yes.

781
01:02:21,480 --> 01:02:22,920
SIMON: So the formula works?

782
01:02:22,960 --> 01:02:25,440
Oh, kiss me again.

783
01:02:27,720 --> 01:02:29,160
-No.
-Make up your mind.

784
01:02:29,160 --> 01:02:34,200
Oh, it's--I have to
figure out the order...

785
01:02:34,240 --> 01:02:36,920
before the formula works,
and I'm not giving it to him.

786
01:02:36,960 --> 01:02:38,960
-Tretiak will find you.
-No.

787
01:02:39,000 --> 01:02:41,400
He found me,
and that's hard to do.

788
01:02:41,440 --> 01:02:45,400
-I found you.
-Yes, you did.

789
01:02:45,440 --> 01:02:46,720
What do you need?

790
01:02:51,120 --> 01:02:53,000
I need some time...

791
01:02:53,040 --> 01:02:54,280
and I need...

792
01:02:56,520 --> 01:02:59,360
I need a place to work...

793
01:02:59,400 --> 01:03:00,960
and...

794
01:03:01,960 --> 01:03:04,120
EMMA:
Where's everyone going?

795
01:03:04,160 --> 01:03:07,400
SIMON: To their country
relatives to cut firewood.

796
01:03:07,440 --> 01:03:09,080
There's no heat in the city.

797
01:03:10,960 --> 01:03:13,280
[Dialing telephone]

798
01:03:13,320 --> 01:03:14,720
[Loud rock music playing]

799
01:03:18,880 --> 01:03:20,920
How long will it take you
to finish the formula?

800
01:03:20,960 --> 01:03:22,520
I don't know.

801
01:03:22,560 --> 01:03:25,640
Two hours, maybe.
I don't know.

802
01:03:25,680 --> 01:03:28,240
Should be enough time to get
our passports together...

803
01:03:28,280 --> 01:03:31,120
and for us to get married.

804
01:03:31,160 --> 01:03:33,760
-We're getting married?
-Yes.

805
01:03:34,880 --> 01:03:38,040
I want you to be
Mrs. Martin de Porres.

806
01:03:41,720 --> 01:03:44,120
-You're not Martin.
-No.

807
01:03:45,560 --> 01:03:46,720
Who are you?

808
01:03:50,080 --> 01:03:51,480
I don't have a name.

809
01:03:53,040 --> 01:03:54,240
That's sad.

810
01:03:54,280 --> 01:03:56,560
Will you have a name
when we get home?

811
01:03:56,600 --> 01:03:58,440
I don't have a home.

812
01:03:58,480 --> 01:04:00,160
When we get back...

813
01:04:00,200 --> 01:04:02,400
you do the science,
I'll do the math.

814
01:04:02,440 --> 01:04:04,120
We'll market your formula
around the world.

815
01:04:04,680 --> 01:04:07,280
We'll make a fortune,
and then...

816
01:04:08,920 --> 01:04:10,080
we'll see.

817
01:04:11,440 --> 01:04:13,080
OK?

818
01:04:21,320 --> 01:04:22,600
Emma!

819
01:04:24,360 --> 01:04:26,240
[Horn honking]

820
01:04:39,880 --> 01:04:41,440
MAN: No trouble, OK?

821
01:04:44,840 --> 01:04:48,040
If you want to live,
never leave my side.

822
01:05:34,200 --> 01:05:35,360
Ohh!

823
01:05:38,600 --> 01:05:39,880
[Splash]

824
01:06:43,920 --> 01:06:45,240
[Music blaring]
Spice room, sun room...

825
01:06:45,280 --> 01:06:47,320
Shadow room, night...

826
01:06:48,720 --> 01:06:50,440
EMMA: I've got you.

827
01:06:56,680 --> 01:06:58,200
EMMA: Come on.

828
01:07:02,360 --> 01:07:04,200
Here we go. Up.

829
01:07:07,560 --> 01:07:10,120
We've gotta get you warm.

830
01:07:17,800 --> 01:07:19,560
We're almost there.

831
01:07:42,680 --> 01:07:43,840
EMMA: Come on.

832
01:07:45,160 --> 01:07:47,040
Come on.

833
01:07:52,200 --> 01:07:55,240
You'll wait till Christ
comes to Moscow.

834
01:07:55,280 --> 01:07:57,880
Elevator was made of mahogany.

835
01:07:57,920 --> 01:08:00,000
Tenants used it
for firewood last winter.

836
01:08:00,040 --> 01:08:01,560
EMMA: We need your help.

837
01:08:01,600 --> 01:08:04,280
He fell in the river,
and he's freezing.

838
01:08:04,320 --> 01:08:05,960
-Need clothes.
-We're just people--

839
01:08:06,000 --> 01:08:10,280
You're not people.
You're Americans.

840
01:08:10,320 --> 01:08:13,440
Yes, but we ran into trouble
with your Mafia.

841
01:08:13,480 --> 01:08:14,560
[Tires screech]

842
01:08:35,200 --> 01:08:36,319
[Speaking Russian]

843
01:08:36,319 --> 01:08:38,000
[Speaking Russian]

844
01:08:44,279 --> 01:08:48,680
She disapproves of what I do,
but eats the bread it buys her.

845
01:08:50,600 --> 01:08:52,720
No heat for sale...

846
01:08:52,760 --> 01:08:54,600
but these clothes
will make him warm.

847
01:08:54,640 --> 01:08:58,000
[Speaking Russian]

848
01:08:59,840 --> 01:09:02,359
I tell her, Mashenka,
go back to bed.

849
01:09:02,399 --> 01:09:04,399
She's always puttering around.

850
01:09:08,040 --> 01:09:11,880
It's here.
Built to escape Secret Police.

851
01:09:11,920 --> 01:09:13,359
In you go.

852
01:09:27,440 --> 01:09:29,760
EMMA: You've got hypothermia.

853
01:09:29,800 --> 01:09:32,200
We have to get
these wet clothes off...

854
01:09:33,560 --> 01:09:35,040
keep you warm.

855
01:09:35,480 --> 01:09:37,640
ILYA: They must be in
one of these buildings.

856
01:09:37,680 --> 01:09:39,279
Check every apartment.

857
01:09:41,160 --> 01:09:44,200
EMMA: How you doing? 
Talk to me.

858
01:09:44,240 --> 01:09:46,960
SIMON: Snug as a bug in a rug.

859
01:09:54,680 --> 01:09:58,000
OK. We're gonna...

860
01:09:58,040 --> 01:10:01,920
We're gonna have to do this
before your body temperature...

861
01:10:01,960 --> 01:10:04,800
falls below 95 degrees.

862
01:10:17,080 --> 01:10:19,920
MAN: Two kids
talking about foreigners.

863
01:10:26,200 --> 01:10:28,440
[Bell rings]

864
01:10:28,480 --> 01:10:30,120
ILYA: Listen to me, tenants!

865
01:10:30,960 --> 01:10:33,120
Show me where
the Americans are...

866
01:10:33,160 --> 01:10:37,000
and you'll be paid
in American dollars.

867
01:10:37,040 --> 01:10:39,320
Five hundred bucks reward.

868
01:10:39,320 --> 01:10:40,520
Daddy...

869
01:10:42,040 --> 01:10:45,120
have you seen, by chance,
two Americans?

870
01:10:45,160 --> 01:10:47,840
Just one American
and one polar bear.

871
01:10:47,880 --> 01:10:49,640
[Woman laughs]

872
01:10:49,680 --> 01:10:51,480
Do we get 250?

873
01:10:59,800 --> 01:11:02,040
[Woman speaking Russian]

874
01:11:10,440 --> 01:11:11,560
ILYA: We check upstairs.

875
01:11:12,720 --> 01:11:13,880
[Door closes]

876
01:11:23,480 --> 01:11:24,920
EMMA: What's your name?

877
01:11:28,200 --> 01:11:29,600
Who are you really?

878
01:11:31,560 --> 01:11:32,680
Simon.

879
01:11:32,720 --> 01:11:33,920
Simon?

880
01:11:34,840 --> 01:11:37,800
So you are named for a saint.

881
01:11:37,840 --> 01:11:39,600
No, Simon the magician.

882
01:11:40,480 --> 01:11:42,520
I did tricks...

883
01:11:42,560 --> 01:11:46,000
tricks for Agnes...
and that's how I got things.

884
01:11:46,040 --> 01:11:49,880
Priests took everything,
took Agnes.

885
01:11:49,920 --> 01:11:51,920
Dogs too big.

886
01:11:51,960 --> 01:11:54,920
Teeth. Teeth.

887
01:11:54,960 --> 01:11:56,680
She fell.

888
01:11:56,720 --> 01:11:58,040
I escaped.

889
01:11:59,440 --> 01:12:00,960
I always escape.

890
01:12:01,880 --> 01:12:04,280
I don't believe in magic
anymore.

891
01:12:05,880 --> 01:12:07,160
EMMA: I do.

892
01:12:09,720 --> 01:12:12,320
I've never felt
like this before.

893
01:12:13,480 --> 01:12:14,600
How?

894
01:12:15,960 --> 01:12:17,440
I'm freezing.

895
01:12:21,880 --> 01:12:23,560
WOMAN: These are here!

896
01:12:30,400 --> 01:12:33,200
EMMA: We gotta get out of here.
Are you OK?

897
01:12:33,240 --> 01:12:35,320
They're coming.

898
01:12:36,280 --> 01:12:38,880
WOMAN: Americans are here!

899
01:12:38,920 --> 01:12:41,240
EMMA:
Hurry. Here, put this on.

900
01:12:46,840 --> 01:12:47,960
MAN: Ilya!

901
01:12:52,760 --> 01:12:54,240
[Siren]

902
01:13:01,040 --> 01:13:02,280
Upstairs. Go!

903
01:13:19,600 --> 01:13:21,120
EMMA: Maybe we can jump.

904
01:13:22,200 --> 01:13:23,680
Let's jump.

905
01:13:27,640 --> 01:13:29,400
Come on.

906
01:13:54,040 --> 01:13:55,200
Wait.

907
01:14:11,800 --> 01:14:13,680
We need her alive, idiot.

908
01:14:15,760 --> 01:14:17,400
SIMON: Embassy's east of here.

909
01:14:26,200 --> 01:14:27,600
[Arguing in Russian]

910
01:14:35,960 --> 01:14:37,760
WOMAN: You're late.
Where have you been?

911
01:14:38,520 --> 01:14:40,160
I've been waiting two hours.

912
01:14:40,200 --> 01:14:43,720
Come on. I've got some beautiful
paintings for you to buy.

913
01:14:43,760 --> 01:14:45,240
In here. Come on. Come on.

914
01:14:50,040 --> 01:14:53,200
Don't fret.
It's just my curator, Toli.

915
01:14:53,240 --> 01:14:55,840
I am Alexa Frankievitch,
but being you're Americans...

916
01:14:55,880 --> 01:14:57,680
you can call me Frankie.

917
01:14:57,720 --> 01:14:59,720
SIMON: OK, Frankie.
I've got money. We want--

918
01:14:59,760 --> 01:15:03,600
FRANKIE: I know. 
The icon of the Virgin of the Damned.

919
01:15:03,640 --> 01:15:06,000
-Are those maps of the tunnels?
-Yes.

920
01:15:06,040 --> 01:15:08,720
We're not here to buy art.
Take us to the American Embassy.

921
01:15:08,760 --> 01:15:11,720
FRANKIE: Right.
I need $10,000 up-front.

922
01:15:11,760 --> 01:15:14,040
SIMON: No.

923
01:15:14,040 --> 01:15:17,440
OK. 7,000 and not a penny less.

924
01:15:17,480 --> 01:15:18,880
TOLI: Shh.

925
01:15:26,160 --> 01:15:27,600
[Whispering] Police.

926
01:15:27,640 --> 01:15:29,600
SIMON: No. Tretiak's goons.

927
01:15:38,360 --> 01:15:39,520
FRANKIE: Wait.

928
01:15:39,560 --> 01:15:42,440
ILYA: Sasha,
go east to the embassy.

929
01:15:42,480 --> 01:15:44,400
-Are we lost?
-What's wrong?

930
01:15:44,440 --> 01:15:47,640
FRANKIE: You're in Russia, sir.
Everything is complicated.

931
01:15:47,640 --> 01:15:48,720
But you know the way?

932
01:15:48,840 --> 01:15:52,280
Like the face
of a Bulgari chronograph.

933
01:16:02,160 --> 01:16:04,000
I remember. This way.

934
01:16:08,200 --> 01:16:10,840
FRANKIE: At last. Water main.

935
01:16:11,600 --> 01:16:13,800
They shut it down
each afternoon in winter.

936
01:16:13,840 --> 01:16:15,400
SIMON: What time do they
turn it back on?

937
01:16:15,440 --> 01:16:18,720
FRANKIE: You have five minutes,
plus or minus.

938
01:16:18,760 --> 01:16:19,840
EMMA: Plus or minus?

939
01:16:19,880 --> 01:16:22,240
TOLI: That means several
minutes earlier or later.

940
01:16:22,240 --> 01:16:25,280
FRANKIE: Don't worry.
Third opening is your embassy.

941
01:16:42,720 --> 01:16:44,560
Quick. Someone's coming.

942
01:16:50,120 --> 01:16:52,600
Come on. Come on.

943
01:17:00,080 --> 01:17:02,040
SIMON: Here's the second one.

944
01:17:02,080 --> 01:17:03,800
Embassy's next.

945
01:17:07,360 --> 01:17:10,880
-About two more minutes.
-Yeah. Unless it's minus.

946
01:17:14,560 --> 01:17:17,160
SIMON: Damn.
It's sealed.

947
01:17:18,640 --> 01:17:20,360
We'll have to go back.

948
01:17:20,400 --> 01:17:21,560
EMMA: Come on.

949
01:17:36,280 --> 01:17:38,240
[Distant rumbling]

950
01:17:44,560 --> 01:17:45,760
Hurry.

951
01:17:55,440 --> 01:17:57,400
SIMON: Up you go.

952
01:18:16,160 --> 01:18:19,080
MAN: Yankee, go home!
Down with Yankee!

953
01:18:19,120 --> 01:18:20,960
[Crowd chanting in Russian]

954
01:18:26,600 --> 01:18:29,760
Embassy's only
about 100 yards away.

955
01:18:29,800 --> 01:18:33,240
There's a car right above us.
Watch your head.

956
01:18:36,640 --> 01:18:38,160
[Hissing]

957
01:18:40,400 --> 01:18:42,320
[Crowd chanting in Russian]

958
01:19:05,240 --> 01:19:07,160
SIMON: I'll create a diversion.

959
01:19:07,200 --> 01:19:09,880
It should take you 10 seconds
to run to those gates.

960
01:19:09,920 --> 01:19:11,800
They'll open them
when they see you coming.

961
01:19:12,680 --> 01:19:14,360
EMMA: OK. I can do that.

962
01:19:14,400 --> 01:19:16,440
You can do it.

963
01:19:16,480 --> 01:19:20,320
Wait. When am I gonna see you?

964
01:19:20,360 --> 01:19:22,280
I'll find you. You found me.

965
01:19:22,320 --> 01:19:23,920
Yeah, I did.

966
01:19:53,000 --> 01:19:54,120
Aah!

967
01:20:24,200 --> 01:20:27,560
EMMA: I'm an American!
Open the gate!

968
01:20:27,600 --> 01:20:30,040
Open the gate!
I'm an American!

969
01:20:30,720 --> 01:20:32,840
MARINE: Back off from the gate.

970
01:20:32,880 --> 01:20:35,720
Back off. I said back off.

971
01:20:36,800 --> 01:20:40,080
Stand back from the gate.

972
01:20:41,720 --> 01:20:43,160
I said back off!

973
01:20:55,640 --> 01:20:57,080
SIMON: She outran you?

974
01:20:57,120 --> 01:20:59,080
How humiliating.

975
01:21:02,800 --> 01:21:05,920
One...shot left.

976
01:21:07,520 --> 01:21:09,480
Can't come
all the way to Russia...

977
01:21:09,520 --> 01:21:12,200
and not play Russian roulette.

978
01:21:12,240 --> 01:21:14,400
Before you shoot me,
want to know where the money is?

979
01:21:14,440 --> 01:21:16,000
[Clicks]

980
01:21:16,040 --> 01:21:17,640
Whose money?

981
01:21:17,680 --> 01:21:19,240
Tretiak's, yours.

982
01:21:19,280 --> 01:21:21,640
He treats you like dirt.
You could have it all.

983
01:21:21,680 --> 01:21:23,160
ILYA: What are you saying?

984
01:21:23,200 --> 01:21:25,320
I'm saying your father
stashed billions...

985
01:21:25,360 --> 01:21:28,240
and I know where it's hidden.
Let's make a deal.

986
01:21:28,280 --> 01:21:31,800
So...where are all those
hidden billions?

987
01:21:32,520 --> 01:21:36,280
I know...but I don't think
I'm gonna tell you.

988
01:21:59,080 --> 01:22:01,440
[Sirens]

989
01:22:04,880 --> 01:22:07,640
MAN: Joseph, what's the holdup?
I said get 'em inside!

990
01:22:07,680 --> 01:22:09,560
DOCTOR: You're worse
than all the others.

991
01:22:09,600 --> 01:22:12,200
However, burns will heal.

992
01:22:12,240 --> 01:22:14,800
Maybe a little chance
of scarring, perhaps...

993
01:22:14,840 --> 01:22:18,080
but all in all,
I'd say he's a very lucky boy.

994
01:22:18,080 --> 01:22:20,360
ILYA: Lucky? Look at me.

995
01:22:21,240 --> 01:22:23,800
I am a damn devil.

996
01:22:23,840 --> 01:22:25,320
TRETIAK: Christ.

997
01:22:28,480 --> 01:22:29,560
Yes?

998
01:22:29,600 --> 01:22:32,600
BOTVIN: I have run every test
on this cold fusion formula...

999
01:22:32,640 --> 01:22:37,000
and must conclude
it is not merely incomplete...

1000
01:22:37,040 --> 01:22:39,240
but rather... 
impossible.

1001
01:22:39,280 --> 01:22:42,920
You may as well try to create
perpetual motion, Mr. Tretiak.

1002
01:22:43,840 --> 01:22:46,560
I invest millions...

1003
01:22:47,720 --> 01:22:50,560
and you can't make it work!

1004
01:22:53,840 --> 01:22:56,640
What are you doing
with my money?

1005
01:22:59,200 --> 01:23:02,880
Do you think it comes so easy?

1006
01:23:02,920 --> 01:23:04,040
No!

1007
01:23:04,080 --> 01:23:06,040
BOTVIN: But, sir...

1008
01:23:06,080 --> 01:23:10,560
I have been working for
nearly two weeks without sleep.

1009
01:23:10,600 --> 01:23:15,000
At first blush, the theorem
appears quite impressiv, convincing.

1010
01:23:15,040 --> 01:23:16,520
It does?

1011
01:23:20,800 --> 01:23:24,920
Yes. It does.

1012
01:23:25,640 --> 01:23:26,920
Good man.

1013
01:23:26,960 --> 01:23:29,520
We can use it
to destroy our enemies.

1014
01:23:31,240 --> 01:23:34,600
TRETIAK: Only Dr. Russell
can spoil my plan.

1015
01:23:34,640 --> 01:23:37,320
If she gets back to London
and speaks to the press...

1016
01:23:37,360 --> 01:23:41,040
YURI: From here to the airport
are three army checkpoints...

1017
01:23:41,080 --> 01:23:42,880
all of them loyal to us.

1018
01:23:42,920 --> 01:23:44,920
TRETIAK: Make certain
they get the message--

1019
01:23:44,960 --> 01:23:47,720
she doesn't leave Moscow alive.

1020
01:23:50,160 --> 01:23:51,360
Mr. President.

1021
01:23:51,400 --> 01:23:54,400
As former Vice-minister
of Energy and Power...

1022
01:23:54,440 --> 01:23:59,520
I hear all manner of schemes
that provide cheaper energy.

1023
01:23:59,560 --> 01:24:03,000
And as our countrymen
freeze to death...

1024
01:24:03,040 --> 01:24:06,360
I've become aware of
a marvelous new technology...

1025
01:24:06,400 --> 01:24:09,240
about which I'm hopelessly
out of my league...

1026
01:24:09,280 --> 01:24:11,920
from a scientific viewpoint.

1027
01:24:11,960 --> 01:24:15,080
That's why I brought
our eminent physicist here...

1028
01:24:15,120 --> 01:24:18,240
Dr. Lev Botvin from
the University of Moscow.

1029
01:24:18,280 --> 01:24:20,760
AIDE: Before we are dazzled
by the good news...

1030
01:24:20,800 --> 01:24:23,360
let's dispense with the bad.

1031
01:24:23,400 --> 01:24:25,520
What is the price
of this marvel?

1032
01:24:25,560 --> 01:24:28,280
YURI: The cost of research
and development are there...

1033
01:24:28,320 --> 01:24:31,880
which is all
you are asked to defray.

1034
01:24:36,760 --> 01:24:39,400
Ten billion in hard currency?

1035
01:24:39,440 --> 01:24:44,360
I can't even pay my teachers,
my miners, my doctors.

1036
01:24:51,560 --> 01:24:53,480
Where are you heading?

1037
01:24:53,520 --> 01:24:56,800
I thought we'd drink
some vodka to get warmer.

1038
01:25:00,840 --> 01:25:03,800
Like the miracle of socialism...

1039
01:25:03,840 --> 01:25:07,040
our miracle
of cold fusion failed.

1040
01:25:07,080 --> 01:25:08,200
But no matter.

1041
01:25:08,240 --> 01:25:12,360
We have sold cold fusion
to President Karpov.

1042
01:25:12,400 --> 01:25:15,800
We will use the scandal
of its failure to destroy him.

1043
01:25:15,840 --> 01:25:18,600
The army must be mobilized
by midnight tomorrow.

1044
01:25:18,640 --> 01:25:22,120
You're a man in a hurry.
That's only one day.

1045
01:25:22,160 --> 01:25:25,440
ILYA: Not now, old witch.
We're working.

1046
01:25:25,480 --> 01:25:26,880
TRETIAK: Yes. Think of it.

1047
01:25:26,920 --> 01:25:32,520
One day, you can be proud again
to be a Russian general...

1048
01:25:32,560 --> 01:25:36,520
with a big nuclear missile
where your prick used to be.

1049
01:25:36,560 --> 01:25:39,560
AIDE: You must complete a form
before you get on a flight home.

1050
01:25:39,600 --> 01:25:41,160
Any medical problems?

1051
01:25:41,200 --> 01:25:42,640
EMMA: I have a heart condition.

1052
01:25:42,680 --> 01:25:45,120
AIDE: Do you need me to arrange
any medication for you?

1053
01:25:46,000 --> 01:25:48,440
EMMA: Well, I haven't
needed a pill.

1054
01:25:48,960 --> 01:25:50,120
That's strange.

1055
01:25:50,160 --> 01:25:52,200
MARINE: Get a form from
table three down the corridor.

1056
01:25:52,240 --> 01:25:53,680
I'll be back in 10 minutes...

1057
01:25:53,720 --> 01:25:55,840
by your side,
all the way to the airport.

1058
01:25:55,880 --> 01:25:57,000
EMMA: Thank you.

1059
01:25:57,040 --> 01:25:59,200
REPORTER: ...Across the street
in central Moscow...

1060
01:25:59,240 --> 01:26:03,680
where a mob attacked several
companies with ties to America.

1061
01:26:03,720 --> 01:26:07,520
Apparently, four U.S. citizens
were injured in the attack.

1062
01:26:07,600 --> 01:26:09,360
I'm told
that all American citizens...

1063
01:26:09,400 --> 01:26:11,920
have been asked to report
to the American embassy...

1064
01:26:11,960 --> 01:26:13,800
for immediate evacuation.

1065
01:26:13,840 --> 01:26:17,000
MAN: [Southern accent]
Excuse me. little lady. You look lost.

1066
01:26:17,040 --> 01:26:19,440
-No, I'm fine.
-May I help you?

1067
01:26:19,440 --> 01:26:24,000
Allow me to introduce myself.
My name is August Christopher.

1068
01:26:24,040 --> 01:26:27,480
Named after Saint Augustine,
who coined my favorite phrase--

1069
01:26:27,520 --> 01:26:29,960
"Give me chastity
and give me constancy...

1070
01:26:30,000 --> 01:26:32,520
"but do not give it yet."

1071
01:26:35,120 --> 01:26:36,440
[Protesters chanting in Russian]

1072
01:26:36,480 --> 01:26:39,880
Simon, I'm on the next flight
out of here.

1073
01:26:39,920 --> 01:26:41,080
Are you coming with me?

1074
01:26:41,120 --> 01:26:44,480
No. But they are.

1075
01:26:50,400 --> 01:26:53,880
I'll need you to develop
a sudden fear of flying.

1076
01:26:53,920 --> 01:26:55,720
Find a quiet room.

1077
01:26:56,560 --> 01:26:58,800
Finish the formula
and fax it back to me.

1078
01:26:58,840 --> 01:27:00,520
My number's on the back.

1079
01:27:00,560 --> 01:27:04,200
I don't understand.
Why are you keeping my cards?

1080
01:27:04,240 --> 01:27:06,000
I've got to deal
with the Russians...

1081
01:27:06,040 --> 01:27:08,040
or you'll never be safe.

1082
01:27:08,080 --> 01:27:09,760
Be good at school.

1083
01:27:09,800 --> 01:27:10,920
Wait.

1084
01:27:13,280 --> 01:27:16,200
-Don't you trust me, darlin'?
-Trust who?

1085
01:27:17,040 --> 01:27:18,720
SIMON: That hurts, Emma.

1086
01:27:18,760 --> 01:27:21,320
EMMA: I'm serious.
What's your name?

1087
01:27:21,360 --> 01:27:24,040
My name is August Christopher.

1088
01:27:24,080 --> 01:27:26,960
Of course I trust you,
August Christopher.

1089
01:27:27,000 --> 01:27:28,920
I mean, Vincent Ferrer...

1090
01:27:28,960 --> 01:27:31,080
I mean, Martin de Porres...

1091
01:27:32,280 --> 01:27:34,040
Thomas More.

1092
01:27:35,160 --> 01:27:38,000
After all,
you are my personal saint.

1093
01:27:38,920 --> 01:27:40,760
You have to be a very good...

1094
01:27:40,800 --> 01:27:44,200
and, usually, a very dead person
to become a saint.

1095
01:27:44,240 --> 01:27:47,720
And more importantly,
you have to work three miracles.

1096
01:27:47,760 --> 01:27:49,960
Now, get to work.

1097
01:27:50,720 --> 01:27:52,320
Who's that man?

1098
01:27:52,360 --> 01:27:54,640
AIDE: You're leaving
on the transport at 9:00, ma'am?

1099
01:27:54,680 --> 01:27:57,560
Probably be your
last chance out of here.

1100
01:27:57,600 --> 01:27:59,040
Better hurry. It's leaving.

1101
01:28:01,320 --> 01:28:03,840
YURI: Your troops
will depose the president...

1102
01:28:03,880 --> 01:28:06,720
and install Ivan Tretiak
as leader of Russia.

1103
01:28:06,760 --> 01:28:11,320
TRETIAK: Moscow must be
ringed with tanks by early evening.

1104
01:28:11,360 --> 01:28:14,560
Don't worry.
The people will follow me.

1105
01:28:14,600 --> 01:28:16,760
They will be crying
for revolution.

1106
01:28:16,800 --> 01:28:19,280
YURI: Still, no one's
guessed the simple truth...

1107
01:28:19,320 --> 01:28:21,320
of where the heating oil went.

1108
01:28:21,360 --> 01:28:23,040
[Laughter]

1109
01:28:25,360 --> 01:28:28,040
TRETIAK: Who would believe
that a sea of oil...

1110
01:28:28,080 --> 01:28:30,640
was hidden under
this very building?

1111
01:28:30,680 --> 01:28:32,240
[Laughter]

1112
01:28:32,280 --> 01:28:35,120
Yuri, I understand
your Nataly is to...

1113
01:28:35,160 --> 01:28:37,640
WOMAN: Francis, you devil...

1114
01:28:37,680 --> 01:28:39,920
I heard you came down here,
and you didn't call me.

1115
01:28:39,960 --> 01:28:43,200
-Hello, Dominic--
-Give me a ring, when you get this, Charles.

1116
01:28:43,240 --> 01:28:45,840
MAN: Lou,
I've heard on the grapevine...

1117
01:28:45,880 --> 01:28:49,080
you're brokering a revolutionary
new energy source.

1118
01:28:49,920 --> 01:28:52,120
If it's as good
as it's cracked up to be...

1119
01:28:52,160 --> 01:28:55,280
I have friends who can double
your best offer...

1120
01:28:55,320 --> 01:28:57,400
on deposit in Zurich...

1121
01:28:57,440 --> 01:29:00,200
within one hour
of delivery and confirmation.

1122
01:29:01,000 --> 01:29:02,120
I'll be waiting.

1123
01:29:13,520 --> 01:29:14,640
[Door opens]

1124
01:29:22,560 --> 01:29:24,280
The work could be here.

1125
01:29:24,320 --> 01:29:26,160
This machine could work,
couldn't it?

1126
01:29:26,200 --> 01:29:28,800
[Guards shouting in Russian]

1127
01:29:28,840 --> 01:29:30,440
Who are you?

1128
01:29:30,480 --> 01:29:32,520
SIMON:
A friend of Dr. Russell's.

1129
01:29:32,560 --> 01:29:33,720
BOTVIN: Dr. Russell?

1130
01:29:35,800 --> 01:29:37,800
What's this equation?

1131
01:29:37,840 --> 01:29:39,160
It's so simple.

1132
01:29:40,560 --> 01:29:42,640
This is the key
to Dr. Russell's formula.

1133
01:29:42,680 --> 01:29:43,960
Yes.

1134
01:29:44,000 --> 01:29:45,680
[Guards speaking Russian]

1135
01:29:45,720 --> 01:29:47,880
The alarm. You had better go.

1136
01:29:47,920 --> 01:29:51,800
I need a miracle.
You've got 12 hours.

1137
01:29:53,280 --> 01:29:55,360
But Mr. Tretiak's rally
is tonight.

1138
01:29:55,400 --> 01:29:57,000
Can you make it work?

1139
01:29:58,600 --> 01:29:59,720
Make it work.

1140
01:30:04,080 --> 01:30:05,480
GUARD: What is wrong here?

1141
01:30:05,520 --> 01:30:06,880
BOTVIN: Uh, the alarm...

1142
01:30:09,480 --> 01:30:11,320
Uh...uh...

1143
01:30:12,040 --> 01:30:13,440
I tripped.

1144
01:30:21,920 --> 01:30:25,320
[Russian accent]
You are Nikolai Petrovich.

1145
01:30:25,360 --> 01:30:27,000
You are Nikolai Provovich--

1146
01:30:27,040 --> 01:30:28,200
Petrovich.

1147
01:30:30,320 --> 01:30:31,440
[Doorbell buzzes]

1148
01:30:38,840 --> 01:30:40,800
Tunnel built by KGB...

1149
01:30:42,960 --> 01:30:45,240
Leads to machine room
in Kremlin.

1150
01:30:45,280 --> 01:30:49,320
SIMON: Do you know where
the president's quarters are?

1151
01:30:49,360 --> 01:30:53,160
FRANKIE:
President Karpov is there.

1152
01:30:53,200 --> 01:30:57,200
But there are many guards,
so I suggest--

1153
01:30:57,240 --> 01:30:59,160
An alternate route?

1154
01:30:59,200 --> 01:31:02,000
Money. 
Now.

1155
01:31:03,880 --> 01:31:05,400
SIMON: Oh, ye of little faith.

1156
01:31:08,000 --> 01:31:10,600
NEWSWOMAN:
Russia stands tonight...

1157
01:31:10,640 --> 01:31:13,360
on the brink
of a second revolution.

1158
01:31:13,400 --> 01:31:15,840
As the number of deaths
from freezing mounts...

1159
01:31:15,880 --> 01:31:17,760
hundreds of thousands
of protesters...

1160
01:31:17,800 --> 01:31:19,880
have taken to the streets.

1161
01:31:19,920 --> 01:31:21,480
Even as
Russian President Karpov...

1162
01:31:21,520 --> 01:31:23,680
is promising
a mysterious solution...

1163
01:31:23,720 --> 01:31:25,560
to the crippling
heating-oil shortage...

1164
01:31:25,600 --> 01:31:27,720
troops opposed
to the elected government...

1165
01:31:27,760 --> 01:31:30,000
and led
by General Leo Sklarov...

1166
01:31:30,000 --> 01:31:32,680
have begun to ring
the Russian capital city.

1167
01:31:32,720 --> 01:31:34,600
Angry, frightened citizens...

1168
01:31:34,640 --> 01:31:37,320
are gathering outside
the Kremlin in Red Square...

1169
01:31:37,360 --> 01:31:39,120
but they're not braving
the bitter cold...

1170
01:31:39,120 --> 01:31:41,160
for yet another political rally.

1171
01:31:41,200 --> 01:31:44,520
They've been drawn here by
the promise of a revelation...

1172
01:31:44,560 --> 01:31:45,920
whatever that may be...

1173
01:31:45,960 --> 01:31:48,360
in what's become
a life-and-death struggle...

1174
01:31:48,400 --> 01:31:51,280
for the future
of democracy in Russia.

1175
01:32:00,880 --> 01:32:02,320
[Protesters shouting
in Russian]

1176
01:32:21,960 --> 01:32:23,120
[Door shuts]

1177
01:33:03,600 --> 01:33:06,320
SIMON: Mr. President?
I'm your friend.

1178
01:33:06,320 --> 01:33:08,080
KARPOV: What do you want?

1179
01:33:09,880 --> 01:33:13,040
I want to help you
to destroy Tretiak.

1180
01:33:13,080 --> 01:33:14,800
I need you to listen
for about 30 seconds.

1181
01:33:16,560 --> 01:33:19,240
I'm all right. Stay outside.

1182
01:33:19,280 --> 01:33:21,200
Please, continue.

1183
01:33:21,240 --> 01:33:24,560
Tonight you'll stand trial
in Red Square before the world.

1184
01:33:24,560 --> 01:33:27,800
Whatever Tretiak accuses you of,
I need you to admit to it.

1185
01:33:27,840 --> 01:33:29,720
Agree with this criminal?

1186
01:33:29,760 --> 01:33:32,120
If you want
to destroy Tretiak...yes.

1187
01:33:48,600 --> 01:33:50,720
Gruschev,
take Mr. Karpov downstairs.

1188
01:33:50,760 --> 01:33:51,920
The wife stays here.

1189
01:33:51,920 --> 01:33:54,000
[Mrs. Karpov speaking Russian]

1190
01:33:54,040 --> 01:33:57,320
Get your hands off!
What you are doing is illegal!

1191
01:33:57,360 --> 01:33:59,240
The people won't stand for it!

1192
01:33:59,280 --> 01:34:02,600
The people are too cold
to stop it. Who are you?

1193
01:34:16,280 --> 01:34:18,960
CROWD: Tretiak!
Tretiak! Tretiak!

1194
01:34:23,480 --> 01:34:25,400
[Crowd cheering]

1195
01:34:33,720 --> 01:34:35,760
Friends...

1196
01:34:35,800 --> 01:34:37,640
countrymen...

1197
01:34:37,680 --> 01:34:39,760
Russians!

1198
01:34:49,040 --> 01:34:53,200
You heard about this morning's
sensational events.

1199
01:34:53,240 --> 01:34:56,240
Many shocking documents
were recovered...

1200
01:34:56,280 --> 01:34:58,440
from the president's
secret files...

1201
01:34:58,480 --> 01:35:01,040
locked within his private safe.

1202
01:35:01,040 --> 01:35:05,800
The documents which will be
published in today's papers...

1203
01:35:05,840 --> 01:35:10,000
prove that the traitor Karpov...

1204
01:35:10,000 --> 01:35:13,720
was about to steal
over 40 trillion...

1205
01:35:13,760 --> 01:35:16,520
of our precious
Russian rubles...

1206
01:35:16,560 --> 01:35:21,040
in a reckless scheme
to save his hide!

1207
01:35:21,040 --> 01:35:22,960
To add insult...

1208
01:35:23,000 --> 01:35:25,840
millions of dollars
were to be paid...

1209
01:35:25,840 --> 01:35:28,840
to this international criminal!

1210
01:35:28,880 --> 01:35:31,120
[Crowd reacting]

1211
01:35:35,520 --> 01:35:37,480
TRETIAK: And for what
was your president...

1212
01:35:37,520 --> 01:35:41,520
hoping to bankrupt
our national treasury?

1213
01:35:41,520 --> 01:35:46,640
What you see is a fairy tale
called cold fusion.

1214
01:35:46,640 --> 01:35:51,400
You pass electric current
into the machine...

1215
01:35:51,440 --> 01:35:55,520
and there is supposed
to be a chemical reaction.

1216
01:35:55,560 --> 01:35:57,080
Watch. [Beep]

1217
01:35:57,120 --> 01:36:00,600
It can't even light up
a tiny light bulb!

1218
01:36:00,640 --> 01:36:03,000
Do you dare deny this,
Mr. Karpov?

1219
01:36:03,040 --> 01:36:05,160
KARPOV: Absolutely not!

1220
01:36:05,200 --> 01:36:07,440
I proudly admit it!

1221
01:36:07,440 --> 01:36:10,440
TRETIAK:
But enough puny failure.

1222
01:36:10,480 --> 01:36:12,520
Failure's in the past!

1223
01:36:12,560 --> 01:36:15,680
Begging is behind us!

1224
01:36:15,720 --> 01:36:20,320
The balance of power
is about to shift!

1225
01:36:51,880 --> 01:36:53,840
Miracle one.

1226
01:36:58,040 --> 01:37:00,680
CROWD: Karpov! Karpov!

1227
01:37:00,720 --> 01:37:02,560
Karpov! Karpov!

1228
01:37:02,600 --> 01:37:04,760
Karpov! Karpov!

1229
01:37:04,800 --> 01:37:06,880
Karpov! Karpov!

1230
01:37:06,920 --> 01:37:09,040
Karpov! Karpov!

1231
01:37:09,080 --> 01:37:11,720
Karpov! Karpov!

1232
01:37:11,760 --> 01:37:13,560
Karpov! Karpov!

1233
01:37:13,600 --> 01:37:15,920
Karpov! Karpov!

1234
01:37:15,920 --> 01:37:17,880
Karpov! Karpov!

1235
01:37:24,880 --> 01:37:25,960
TRETIAK: Ilya! Ilya!

1236
01:37:26,000 --> 01:37:27,320
ILYA: Go! Go!

1237
01:37:27,360 --> 01:37:28,840
Go, go, go!

1238
01:37:30,320 --> 01:37:34,600
SKLAROV: I order all troops
loyal to mother Russia...

1239
01:37:34,640 --> 01:37:37,960
to seize the criminal Tretiak!

1240
01:37:43,280 --> 01:37:44,840
A thousand apologies,
Mr. President.

1241
01:37:44,880 --> 01:37:48,120
There was a miscommunication 
somewhere in the chain of command.

1242
01:37:54,320 --> 01:37:55,680
[Thinking]
Miracle two.

1243
01:37:55,760 --> 01:37:58,840
NEWSWOMAN: The billionaire
industrialist and his son, Ilya,...

1244
01:37:58,880 --> 01:38:01,320
were taken to the infamous
Lubyanka prison...

1245
01:38:01,360 --> 01:38:05,520
where they await trial
along with General Leo Sklarov.

1246
01:38:05,520 --> 01:38:09,160
Moscow woke today to the
forgotten sensation of warmth...

1247
01:38:09,200 --> 01:38:11,360
as millions of gallons
of heating oil...

1248
01:38:11,400 --> 01:38:14,960
flowed from a storage depot discovered 
beneath Tretiak's riverside mansion.

1249
01:38:14,960 --> 01:38:17,520
INSPECTOR: He made no threat
to contact you in the future?

1250
01:38:18,360 --> 01:38:19,720
EMMA: He never had the chance.

1251
01:38:19,760 --> 01:38:21,200
You'll tell us
if he does make contact?

1252
01:38:21,440 --> 01:38:23,920
- EMMA: Oh, yes. 
- Which he may well do.

1253
01:38:24,440 --> 01:38:26,360
He's a proper rogue, you see.

1254
01:38:26,400 --> 01:38:29,840
He charms women,
this so-called Saint.

1255
01:38:29,880 --> 01:38:32,680
It seems it's his stock
in trade. No offense.

1256
01:38:32,720 --> 01:38:36,400
Well, I am offended.
All I got from this Saint...

1257
01:38:36,440 --> 01:38:38,760
was a series
of near-death experiences.

1258
01:38:38,800 --> 01:38:40,600
Count yourself lucky.

1259
01:38:40,600 --> 01:38:44,080
Look, I have a very important
conference I must prepare for.

1260
01:38:44,120 --> 01:38:46,360
INSPECTOR: We understand.
You have a life.

1261
01:38:46,400 --> 01:38:48,040
WOMAN: We appreciate
your taking the time.

1262
01:38:48,080 --> 01:38:49,520
EMMA: No problem.

1263
01:38:55,760 --> 01:38:57,680
INSPECTOR:
She's in love with him.

1264
01:39:54,240 --> 01:39:55,640
[Giggling]

1265
01:40:05,240 --> 01:40:07,960
SIMON: I wanted to call you
and tell you everything.

1266
01:40:08,000 --> 01:40:09,160
It hasn't been safe.

1267
01:40:09,200 --> 01:40:11,720
EMMA: I couldn't stop
thinking about you.

1268
01:40:13,880 --> 01:40:18,720
SIMON:
So...have you been busy?

1269
01:40:18,760 --> 01:40:20,920
EMMA: Yeah.
I've been working real hard.

1270
01:40:20,920 --> 01:40:23,640
Thank God I have my cards back.

1271
01:40:23,640 --> 01:40:27,120
SIMON: You don't believe in
this cold fusion mumbo jumbo?

1272
01:40:27,160 --> 01:40:29,720
You know,
you're a very pretty lady.

1273
01:40:29,760 --> 01:40:31,960
EMMA: Oh, my God.

1274
01:40:32,000 --> 01:40:33,400
That was you?

1275
01:40:34,360 --> 01:40:36,720
SIMON: That's who I thought
Dr. Russell would like.

1276
01:40:37,760 --> 01:40:40,240
I thought you were
some old biddy...

1277
01:40:40,280 --> 01:40:43,520
not some gorgeous
soon-to-be-trillionaire.

1278
01:40:43,560 --> 01:40:46,360
You know you're going to be
the richest woman in the world.

1279
01:40:46,400 --> 01:40:47,480
EMMA: I am?

1280
01:40:47,520 --> 01:40:50,320
SIMON: Why do you think
I'm hanging around?

1281
01:40:56,520 --> 01:40:57,600
-Emma.
-Yeah?

1282
01:40:57,640 --> 01:40:59,320
My life is very strange.

1283
01:41:00,240 --> 01:41:01,520
I just...

1284
01:41:05,320 --> 01:41:07,400
I don't do anything normal.

1285
01:41:07,440 --> 01:41:08,920
I'm--I can't even--

1286
01:41:08,960 --> 01:41:12,280
I know. I know you.

1287
01:41:13,440 --> 01:41:15,760
I know your life.

1288
01:41:15,800 --> 01:41:18,320
-What do you want?
-I want you.

1289
01:41:18,360 --> 01:41:20,320
For how long?

1290
01:41:20,360 --> 01:41:22,280
It doesn't matter.

1291
01:41:28,920 --> 01:41:30,560
Tell me you love me.

1292
01:41:32,400 --> 01:41:34,000
I--I love you.

1293
01:41:35,040 --> 01:41:36,160
Simon.

1294
01:41:37,560 --> 01:41:39,680
I love you, Simon.

1295
01:41:40,880 --> 01:41:42,840
Miracle three.

1296
01:42:05,400 --> 01:42:07,320
